  "texts": [
    "Readers familiar with HF may wish to skip or skim this section, and jump straight to the details of the implementation in TBG (see Sec.",
    "3.3).Consider a Hamiltonian with kinetic energy T and two-particle interaction V,Ĥ = T + V = ab T ab ĉ † a ĉb + 1 2 abcd V ab,cd ĉ † a ĉ † b ĉd ĉc,(30)where a, b,... denote single-particle orbitals, and the two-electron interaction integrals are V ab,cd:= ⟨ab| V |cd⟩.",
    "These interaction matrix elements satisfy V ab,cd = V ba,dc = V * cd,ab but are not anti-symmetrized for fermion exchange.",
    "Hartree-Fock is a variational approximation that optimizes the ground state energy within the manifold of Slater determinants: states that can be written as|Ψ⟩ = 1≤i≤Ne d † i |0⟩for N e particles and some electron creation operators d † i that satisfy { di, d † j } = δ ij.",
    "(These are sometimes also referred to as Gaussian states, since they satisfy Wick's theorem: the expectation value of 2n-fermion operators factor into sums of permutations of all the different pairings into products of n two-fermion operator expectation values.)"
  ],
